         "ReleaseNotes": "Highlights%20since%20R595%20Beta%20Release%2C%20595.45.04%20%3Cul%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20regression%20introduced%20in%20the%20580.119.02%20driver%20release%20which%20caused%20some%20X11%20compositors%20%28e.g.%20picom%2C%20Xfwm%29%20to%20blink%3A%20%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//github.com/NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules/issues/986%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3Ehttps%3A//github.com/NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules/issues/986%3C/a%3E%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//github.com/yshui/picom/issues/1488%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3Ehttps%3A//github.com/yshui/picom/issues/1488%3C/a%3E%3C/li%3E%20%09%20%09%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20would%20prevent%20kwin_wayland%20from%20being%20able%20to%20wake%20up%20display%20under%20certain%20scenarios.%20%20%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/bug-external-monitor-fails-to-wake-up-from-powersave-mode-if-refresh-rate-is-higher-than-30hz/316612%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3Ehttps%3A//forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/bug-external-monitor-fails-to-wake-up-from-powersave-mode-if-refresh-rate-is-higher-than-30hz/316612%3C/a%3E%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%3C/li%3E%20%09%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20causes%20a%20kernel%20crash%20when%20display%20docks%20or%20other%20DisplayPort%20MST%20configurations%20are%20disconnected%20from%20the%20GPU.%20%20%20%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/kernel-null-pointer-dereference-in-nvidia-modeset-during-thunderbolt-dock-disconnect/359280%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3Ehttps%3A//forums.developer.nvidia.com/t/kernel-null-pointer-dereference-in-nvidia-modeset-during-thunderbolt-dock-disconnect/359280%3C/a%3E%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%3C/li%3E%20%09%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20caused%20kernel%20panics%20on%20Linux%20kernels%20configured%20with%20CONFIG_RANDSTRUCT_FULL%20or%20CONFIG_RANDSTRUCT_PERFORMANCE%3A%20%20%20%20%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%20%20%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//github.com/NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules/issues/1033%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3Ehttps%3A//github.com/NVIDIA/open-gpu-kernel-modules/issues/1033%3C/a%3E%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%3C/li%3E%20%09%20%09%20%20%20%3Cli%3EImproved%20support%20for%20falling%20back%20to%20system%20memory%20when%20available%20video%20memory%20is%20low%2C%20to%20help%20prevent%20Wayland%20desktop%20freezes.%20%3C/li%3E%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20caused%20nvidia-drm%20to%20report%20errors%20in%20the%20system%20log%20and%20fail%20to%20enumerate%20connectors%20on%20some%20DisplayPort%20MST%20configurations.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20could%20cause%20a%20kernel%20crash%20on%20driver%20initialization%20on%20some%20DisplayPort%20MST%20configurations.%20%3C/li%3E%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20regression%20introduced%20in%20the%20575.xx%20driver%20series%20which%20prevented%20EGL-X11%20applications%20from%20starting%20on%20SLI%20Mosaic.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20could%20cause%20flickering%20in%20VRR%20on%20some%20HDMI%20displays.%3C/li%3E%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20regression%2C%20introduced%20after%20the%20470.xx%20release%20series%2C%20that%20could%20cause%20four%204k%20monitors%2C%20driven%20as%20separate%20X11%20X%20screens%20on%20one%20GPU%2C%20to%20fail%20modeset.%20%3C/li%3E%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20kernel%20module%20build%20issue%20with%20Linux%20kernel%20v6.19.%3C/li%3E%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20could%20cause%20an%20Xid%20error%20to%20be%20reported%20in%20the%20system%20log%2C%20along%20with%20a%20VK_DEVICE_LOST%20API%20error%2C%20when%20repeatedly%20resizing%20Vulkan%20application%20windows.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3C/ul%3E%20%20%20%20%20%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%20%20%20%20Highlights%20from%20R595%20Beta%20Release%2C%20595.45.04%20%20%20%20%20%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EAdded%20support%20for%20the%20%20%20%20%20%20%20VK_EXT_descriptor_heap%20extension.%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20caused%20GPU%20hangs%20and%20%20%20%20%20%20%20Xid%20errors%20in%20Black%20Myth%3A%20Wukong.%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EAdded%20support%20for%20DRI3%20version%201.2.%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EAdded%20support%20for%20the%20%20%20%20%20%20%20VK_EXT_present_timing%20extension.%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20hang%20when%20NVIDIA%20Smooth%20Motion%20%20%20%20%20%20%20is%20enabled%20in%20applications%20that%20use%20VK_KHR_present_id2.%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EModified%20nvidia.ko%20to%20handle%20video%20memory%20preservation%20on%20its%20own%20when%20the%20open%20kernel%20modules%20are%20in%20use%20if%20NVreg_UseKernelSuspendNotifiers%3D1%20is%20enabled.%20When%20the%20proprietary%20driver%20is%20in%20use%2C%20or%20if%20kernel%20suspend%20notifiers%20are%20disabled%2C%20video%20memory%20preservation%20requires%20using%20the%20/proc/driver/nvidia/suspend%20interface%20for%20suspend%20and%20resume%20notifications.%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20See%20the%20chapter%20titled%20%26quot%3BConfiguring%20Power%20Management%20Support%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20README%20for%20more%20information.%20%20%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EEnabled%20the%20nvidia-drm.ko%20modeset%3D1%20parameter%20by%20default.%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3EUpdated%20the%20driver%20to%20allow%20nvidia-smi%20to%20reset%20GPUs%20while%20nvidia-drm%20is%20loaded%20with%20the%20modeset%3D1%20parameter%20enabled%2C%20as%20long%20as%20no%20other%20processes%20are%20using%20the%20GPU.%20%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cli%3EAdded%20a%20new%20application%20profile%20-%20CudaNoStablePerfLimit%20-%20that%20allows%20CUDA-using%20apps%20to%20reach%20P0%20PState.%20See%20the%20%27Application%20Profiles%27%20appendix%20of%20the%20driver%20README%20for%20details.%20%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3ERaised%20the%20minimum%20supported%20Wayland%20version%20to%201.20.%3C/li%3E%20%20%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20prevented%20the%20PowerMizer%20preferred%20mode%20dropdown%20menu%20in%20the%20nvidia-settings%20control%20panel%20from%20functioning%20correctly%20on%20Wayland.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ERaised%20the%20minimum%20supported%20glibc%20version%20to%202.27.%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EImproved%20the%20performance%20of%20recreating%20Vulkan%20swapchains.%20This%20helps%20prevent%20stuttering%20when%20resizing%20Vulkan%20application%20windows.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3ERaised%20the%20minimum%20supported%20X.Org%20xserver%20version%20to%201.17%20%28video%20driver%20ABI%20version%2019%29.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20caused%20adaptive%20sync%20displays%20to%20go%20blank%20when%20connected%20with%20an%20active%20USB-C-to-HDMI%20adapter.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3Cli%3EFixed%20a%20bug%20that%20could%20cause%20Vulkan%20swapchains%20to%20stop%20presenting%20new%20frames%20on%20X11.%20%3C/li%3E%20%3C/ul%3E",
         "OtherNotes": "Note%20that%20%20many%20Linux%20distributions%20provide%20their%20own%20packages%20of%20the%20NVIDIA%20Linux%20%20Graphics%20Driver%20in%20the%20distribution%27s%20native%20package%20management%20format.%20This%20%20may%20interact%20better%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20distribution%27s%20framework%2C%20and%20you%20may%20%20want%20to%20use%20this%20rather%20than%20NVIDIA%27s%20official%20package.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%20%20%20Also%20note%20%20that%20SuSE%20users%20should%20read%20the%20SuSE%20NVIDIA%20Installer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//en.opensuse.org/SDB%3ANVIDIA_drivers%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3EHOWTO%3C/a%3E%20before%20downloading%20%20the%20driver.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%20%20%20Installation%20%20instructions%3A%20Once%20you%20have%20downloaded%20the%20driver%2C%20change%20to%20the%20directory%20%20containing%20the%20driver%20package%20and%20install%20the%20driver%20by%20running%2C%20as%20root%2C%20sh%20./NVIDIA-Linux-x86_64-595.58.03.run%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%20%20%20One%20of%20the%20%20last%20installation%20steps%20will%20offer%20to%20update%20your%20X%20configuration%20file.%20Either%20%20accept%20that%20offer%2C%20edit%20your%20X%20configuration%20file%20manually%20so%20that%20the%20NVIDIA%20X%20%20driver%20will%20be%20used%2C%20or%20run%20nvidia-xconfig%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%20%20%20Note%20that%20the%20%20list%20of%20supported%20GPU%20products%20is%20provided%20to%20indicate%20which%20GPUs%20are%20supported%20%20by%20a%20particular%20driver%20version.%20Some%20designs%20incorporating%20supported%20GPUs%20may%20%20not%20be%20compatible%20with%20the%20NVIDIA%20Linux%20driver%3A%20in%20particular%2C%20notebook%20and%20%20all-in-one%20desktop%20designs%20with%20switchable%20%28hybrid%29%20or%20Optimus%20graphics%20will%20%20not%20work%20if%20means%20to%20disable%20the%20integrated%20graphics%20in%20hardware%20are%20not%20%20available.%20Hardware%20designs%20will%20vary%20from%20manufacturer%20to%20manufacturer%2C%20so%20%20please%20consu